Best Practices for Validator/Miner Key Management

1) Use a local fully controlled PC for all cold key transactions - Transfer, Stake, Delegate and register

# Updates Summary 17-07-2024 

We think that it's really important to be transparent and keep root-validators up to date, but we also understand that you don't have much time to monitor each update that we make in our subnet. 

So, we've decided to change updates format a bit: we still continue to inform you about big updates, but in addition to that we adding *Updates Summary* rubric, in which once in two month we'll be writing summary about all updates that have happened for the last 2 months.

Two months ago we just released our website app alongside with API for detecting ai-genereated texts, so here is our first summary with updates after that release:

## New Products 
**API Code for Validators** 
A week later after our website released we developed and published api code for validators, so that they could use their bandwidth of It's AI subnet on their own.
Read more: https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1215319932062011464/1244613381512761345
API github: https://github.com/It-s-AI/api

**Bittensor monitor bot **
While there are many services for checking stats about your miners/validators all of them provide it only when you check it on their websites. We've developed a bot for miners, validators and subnet owners to track any changes with their neurons or subnets in real-time (compatible with all subnets). 

For miners it tracks rank change, notifies when miner is in dereg zone or when it's deregged. 

For validators it tracks stack and vtrust change, notifies when validator is in dereg zone/deregged or when lask weight update was more than 1k block ago. Can show vtrusts for all subnets.

For subnet owner it tracks subnet emission/rank change, notify when validators weights changed, can show validators weights on the root network and subnet leaderboard.

Read more: https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1215319932062011464/1257635000585814127
Bot link: https://t.me/bt_monitor_bot

## Subnet Developing
Despite new products we've also worked on the subnet validation process to make it more efficient and attack-resistant.

**Small batches mechanic.** On our webiste/API we query miners with only one text and therefore we had to make sure that miners don't use different solutions from the ones they use to gain their incentive. We adjusted our penalty mechanism with small batches, so that now miners must use the same solution for answering on real queries. 
Read more: https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1215319932062011464/1243201455268302858

**Weights versions.** Despite the fact that we had an autoupdate for validators some of them don't use it and so they can stay outdated for a long time. It makes validation process less transparent and make miners to support several validators versions at the same time. We added an extra version parameter into our Synapse structure and force miners to answer only to those validators, who has version in an acceptable range, so that now if validator is too outdated it just get dereg. 
Read more: https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1215319932062011464/1250762144174182411

**Batch based augmentations.** While before we query all miners with the same texts now we apply different augs for each batch of miners, so that they couldn't cache answers (if one person has a lot of miners) and need to provide compute resources for each miner uid. 
Read more: https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1215319932062011464/1245723459187642460

**Segmentation.** In a few days we are going to release our new 3.0 validation process on testnet in which miners have to solve a harder task - not only determine whether text is ai-generated or not, but they will need to segmentate which part of text is ai-generated.

## Validator & Miner Update - Major - v3.0
@itsai・32 

Text classification is a good and important task, but as we've been working on our product and miners have been improving their solutions we've decided that the time came to make a next step, so we're releasing third generation of validators. 

Link to v3.0 - https://github.com/It-s-AI/llm-detection/tree/v3.0
### Task
Since v3.0 miners still will have to detect whether text was ai-generated or not, but it become a text-segmentation task instead of classification. So, with the third version for each text miners will have to return a list of float numbers - probabilites that i-th word is ai-generated.
### Validation data
For generating validation data we'll be using same Pile dataset with these proportion:
1) 25% of texts will be fully human-written
2) 25% of texts will be fully ai-generated
3) 50% will have a human prefix and then an AI-generated suffix
### Models
We also updated LLMs pool that we used for text completion with new open-source SOTA models (such as gemma2, qwen1.5, qwen2, etc) and removed outdated ones.
### Metrics
To count metrics predictions for each word are concatenated among all batch and then counts same metrics as in previous version (ap score, f1 score, fp score) but already on a word basis.
### Batch size and timeout
We decreased number of samples from 300 to 100 texts per batch, timeout stayed the same (20s).
### Baseline
As a new baseline we use previous baseline model to get probability of text to be ai-generated and then use this proba as proba for each word in the text.
### Timeline
We undertand that miners need time to adjust their solution to segmentation task. So, we firstly release v3 on testnet and give miners two weeks to update their solutions (testnet validator is already running). We'll release it on mainnet on 04-08-2024.

# It's AI Benchmarks
@itsai・32 

We've measured our miners on several academia known benchmarks after OTF request and now happy to announce the results. While below you can read a brief summary, we are welcoming you to read our detailed results of benchmarks scoring, measuring approaches and our metrics in the attached file.

## Benchmarks

### RAID: A Shared Benchmark for Robust Evaluation of Machine-Generated Text Detectors
RAID benchmark is currently the most robust benchmark for ai-detectors evaluation. It addresses the limitations of existing datasets by providing a robust and challenging collection of over 6 million text samples generated by 11 different models across 8 domains, incorporating 11 adversarial attacks and 4 decoding strategies. 
### CUDRT: Benchmarking the Detection of Human vs. Large Language Models Generated Texts. 
The CUDRT (Create, Update, Delete, Rewrite, and Translate) dataset is a comprehensive bilingual benchmark designed to evaluate AI-generated text.  includes diverse data sources such as news,
theses, community posts, wiki entries, medical data, and financial information, with a total of 81,713 Chinese samples and 197,163 English samples (only english texts were used in evaluation).
### GPT-generated Text Detection: Benchmark Dataset and Tensor-based Detection Method (GriD)
GRiD consists of context-prompt pairs sourced from Reddit, featuring responses generated by humans and generated by ChatGPT (GPT-3.5 was used). Total dataset size is 6500 samples.

## Results
While Raid dataset is the biggest and most diversed among them it's the most represantable benchmark for comparing our solution with other ai-detectors with more than 600k samples in test set. Twelve ai-detectors were considered in the work (among them commercial GPTZero, Originality, Winston and ZeroGPT). 

We got accuracy 86.7% (92% on non-attacked texts) at FPR 5% and outperformed all other detectors - second place was Originality with 85.2%. All results were gotten from the official leaderboard where we submitted predictions from top-miners on test set. So, It's AI is officially a new SOTA on RAID benchmark!

In the CUDRT dataset were considered only open-sourced solutions and we took first place in 4 out of 8 tasks and on average outoperfomed best considered solution on 5% of f1-score.

GriD paper contained only comparison of a few trained on the data models (while for us it was out of domain validation), but It's AI was able to outperform them anyway (95% f1-score vs 93% of best solution from the work) and become new SOTA on GriD dataset as well.

## Conclusion
Overall, It's AI become a new SOTA on all three considered benchmarks and showed an impressive quality on out of domain validation. These are very promising results (especially comparison with commercial ai-detectors) and we are hoping to make them even better in the future.

Link to the official RAID leaderboard: https:// raid-bench.xyz/leaderboard?domain=all&decoding=all&repetition=all&attack=all

Text classification is a good and important task, but as we've been working on our product and miners have been improving their solutions we've decided that the time came to make a next step and release the third generation of validators.
